Dar es Salaam. The main opposition party (Chadema) has condemned the arrest of Singida East MP and the party s legal affairs director Tundu Lissu, saying the move aims at frustrating the opposition from advocating for the rule of law in the country.Again, it has condemned the naming of its national chairman Freeman Mbowe for people wanted for interrogation.Speaking at a press conference in the city today, the Chadema secretary-general, Dr Vicent Mashinji, said the two processes intended to wipe out the opposition in the country. "We will not be frustrated, instead these attempts encourage us to fight more for the rule of law and true democracy," he said.